A WOMAN has died and three others were injured after a car collided with a bus.
The incident happened on the southbound M73 at Mollinsburn, North Lanarkshire, at around 5.30pm on Saturday.
A 57-year-old female passenger in the Renault Clio died, and three others were injured.
The 29-year old woman driver was left seriously hurt, and two males - aged 18 and 45 sustained minor injuries. None of the 49 passengers on the coach, nor the driver, were hurt.
The road was closed until shortly before midnight to allow for a full crash investigation to take place.
A spokeswoman for Police Scotland said: “We are appealing for witnesses to this crash and ask that anyone who can help get in touch with Police Scotland at Motherwell through 101.”
